Comment: The only funny parts to me were the Darth Vader breathing part and the barfing robot part.  Other than that, the creepiness of the "Uncanny Valley" effect kinda ruins it for me.  Of course, it's just another film slapped in 3D that probably doesn't even utilize that feature well.  I don't mean to be so critical, and it's just my opinion, but I wish Disney would spend time and money on ground-breaking 3D animation.  I mean like the original Toy Story groundbreaking.

Title: MARS NEEDS MOMS Trailer #1
Comment: @LucidDivinity In animation, we call it "Uncanny Valley."  It's usually what we try to avoid, just BECAUSE it's so creepy, but seems like these guys missed the memo.  The unspoken general rule is either go for a serious theme with the more hyperrealistic, or be funny with the more cartoonish.  It doesn't work well to make the "hyperrealistic cartoon."

Yes, it doesn't look as colorful and/or cartoon-y like Toy Story or Tangled, but that, I believe, was to be expected coming from the same studio behind Polar Express and A Christmas Carol. Besides, you can't just judge a movie by its imagery, like how you can't judge a book simply by its cover. One must analyze a motion picture by its own merits; that also holds true to all other movies in existence.
